This paper deals with natural language processing and deep neural networks, which are commonly associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper's focus on historical spelling normalization suggests that it may be more likely to fall under cs.CL or cs.LG, but the use of multi-task learning and deep neural networks could also make it relevant to cs.AI and cs.NE.
